				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/edrobot" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(413055); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=413055&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205728" alt="Edrobot" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=413055)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/edrobot" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(413055); return false;" >Edrobot</a></span> <span class="odate time_1317753955 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Oct 2011 18:45</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1273552">
									

<p>I dunno, I just think that a Die Hard parody/homage/pastiche would be the wrong place to throw it a jab at a <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SitcomArchNemesis">Sitcom Arch-Nemesis</a>, beacuse I feel there are only three ways it could work.</p>
<ol>
<li>Edison has to choose between saving Roadrunner and saving a McGuffin of some sort, so naturally he lets Roadrunner fall <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">to his death. This would probably piss off Roadrunner's writer in all sorts of ways so I'm not doing that.</span> <em>Actually I could probably do this if he got a comedicly painful injury instead of dying.</em></li>
<li>He's working for the villains. As much as I (or, rather, Edison) jokes about this, I kinda doubt he would actually sell out the Foundation like that. And even if he really was as two-faced as Edison believes he is, why the hell would he want to release someone who could destroy the world? It's not a very good survival instinct.</li>
<li>Edison only thinks he's working for the villains. Okay, this one could also work, but only if I use it sparingly.</li>
</ol>

							</div>

								
